TY  - JOUR
TI  - Expansion Paths for Some Production Functions
AU  - Heady, Earl O.
AU  - Pesek, John
AB  - [This article reviews the empirical nature of isoclines or expansion paths from production functions derived from experiments. The algebraic and geometric nature of isoclines is explained for conditions under which interaction is both present and absent among the production factors analyzed, the economic implication of the various families of isoclines also is explained. The production functions for which the isoclines are derived come from physical producing units, rather than from firms or industries.]
